https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aler.name: alert
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aler.description: A type of live region with important, and usually time-sensitive, information. See related alertdialog and status.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aler.name: alertdialog
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aler.description: A type of dialog that contains an alert message, where initial focus goes to an element within the dialog. See related alert and dialog.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#appl.name: application
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#appl.description: A structure containing one or more focusable elements requiring user input, such as keyboard or gesture events, that do not follow a standard interaction pattern supported by a widget role.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#arti.name: article
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#arti.description: A section of a page that consists of a composition that forms an independent part of a document, page, or site.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#bann.name: banner
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#bann.description: A region that contains mostly site-oriented content, rather than page-specific content.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#butt.name: button
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#butt.description: An input that allows for user-triggered actions when clicked or pressed. See related link.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#cell.name: cell
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#cell.description: A cell in a tabular container. See related gridcell.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#chec.name: checkbox
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#chec.description: A checkable input that has three possible values: true, false, or mixed.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#colu.name: columnheader
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#colu.description: A cell containing header information for a column.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comb.name: combobox
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comb.description: A composite widget containing a single-line textbox and another element, such as a listbox or grid, that can dynamically pop up to help the user set the value of the textbox.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comm.name: command
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comm.description: A form of widget that performs an action but does not receive input data.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comp.name: complementary
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comp.description: A supporting section of the document, designed to be complementary to the main content at a similar level in the DOM hierarchy, but remains meaningful when separated from the main content.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comp.name: composite
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#comp.description: A widget that may contain navigable descendants or owned children.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#cont.name: contentinfo
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#cont.description: A large perceivable region that contains information about the parent document.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#defi.name: definition
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#defi.description: A definition of a term or concept. See related term.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#dial.name: dialog
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#dial.description: A dialog is a descendant window of the primary window of a web application. For HTML pages, the primary application window is the entire web document, i.e., the body element.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#dire.name: directory
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#dire.description: A list of references to members of a group, such as a static table of contents.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#docu.name: document
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#docu.description: An element containing content that assistive technology users may want to browse in a reading mode.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#feed.name: feed
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#feed.description: A scrollable list of articles where scrolling may cause articles to be added to or removed from either end of the list.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#figu.name: figure
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#figu.description: A perceivable section of content that typically contains a graphical document, images, code snippets, or example text. The parts of a figure MAY be user-navigable.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#form.name: form
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#form.description: A landmark region that contains a collection of items and objects that, as a whole, combine to create a form. See related search.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#grid.name: grid
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#grid.description: A composite widget containing a collection of one or more rows with one or more cells where some or all cells in the grid are focusable by using methods of two-dimensional navigation, such as directional arrow keys.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#grid.name: gridcell
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#grid.description: A cell in a grid or treegrid.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#grou.name: group
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#grou.description: A set of user interface objects which are not intended to be included in a page summary or table of contents by assistive technologies.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#head.name: heading
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#head.description: A heading for a section of the page.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#img.name: img
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#img.description: A container for a collection of elements that form an image.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#inpu.name: input
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#inpu.description: A generic type of widget that allows user input.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#land.name: landmark
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#land.description: A perceivable section containing content that is relevant to a specific, author-specified  purpose and sufficiently important that users will likely want to be able to navigate to the section easily and to have it listed in a summary of the page. Such a page summary could be generated dynamically by a user agent or assistive technology.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#link.name: link
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#link.description: An interactive reference to an internal or external resource that, when activated, causes the user agent to navigate to that resource. See related button.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#list.name: list
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#list.description: A section containing listitem elements. See related listbox.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#list.name: listbox
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#list.description: A widget that allows the user to select one or more items from a list of choices. See related combobox and list.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#list.name: listitem
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#list.description: A single item in a list or directory.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#log.name: log
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#log.description: A type of live region where new information is added in meaningful order and old information may disappear. See related marquee.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#main.name: main
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#main.description: The main content of a document.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#marq.name: marquee
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#marq.description: A type of live region where non-essential information changes frequently. See related log.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#math.name: math
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#math.description: Content that represents a mathematical expression.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.name: menu
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.description: A type of widget that offers a list of choices to the user.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.name: menubar
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.description: A presentation of menu that usually remains visible and is usually presented horizontally.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.name: menuitem
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.description: An option in a set of choices contained by a menu or menubar.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.name: menuitemcheckbox
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.description: A menuitem with a checkable state whose possible values are true, false, or mixed.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.name: menuitemradio
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#menu.description: A checkable menuitem in a set of elements with the same role, only one of which can be checked at a time.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#navi.name: navigation
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#navi.description: A collection of navigational elements (usually links) for navigating the document or related documents.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#none.name: none
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#none.description: An element whose implicit native role semantics will not be mapped to the accessibility API. See synonym presentation.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#note.name: note
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#note.description: A section whose content is parenthetic or ancillary to the main content of the resource.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#opti.name: option
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#opti.description: A selectable item in a select list.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#pres.name: presentation
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#pres.description: An element whose implicit native role semantics will not be mapped to the accessibility API. See synonym none.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#prog.name: progressbar
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#prog.description: An element that displays the progress status for tasks that take a long time.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#radi.name: radio
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#radi.description: A checkable input in a group of elements with the same role, only one of which can be checked at a time.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#rang.name: range
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#rang.description: An input representing a range of values that can be set by the user.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#regi.name: region
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#regi.description: A perceivable section containing content that is relevant to a specific, author-specified  purpose and sufficiently important that users will likely want to be able to navigate to the section easily and to have it listed in a summary of the page. Such a page summary could be generated dynamically by a user agent or assistive technology.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#role.name: roletype
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#role.description: The base role from which all other roles in this taxonomy inherit.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#row.name: row
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#row.description: A row of cells in a tabular container.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#rowg.name: rowgroup
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#rowg.description: A structure containing one or more row elements in a tabular container.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#rowh.name: rowheader
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#rowh.description: A cell containing header information for a row in a grid.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#scro.name: scrollbar
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#scro.description: A graphical object that controls the scrolling of content within a viewing area, regardless of whether the content is fully displayed within the viewing area.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sear.name: search
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sear.description: A landmark region that contains a collection of items and objects that, as a whole, combine to create a search facility. See related form and searchbox.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sear.name: searchbox
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sear.description: A type of textbox intended for specifying search criteria. See related textbox and search.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sect.name: section
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sect.description: A renderable structural containment unit in a document or application.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sect.name: sectionhead
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sect.description: A structure that labels or summarizes the topic of its related section.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sele.name: select
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sele.description: A form widget that allows the user to make selections from a set of choices.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sepa.name: separator
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#sepa.description: A divider that separates and distinguishes sections of content or groups of menuitems.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#slid.name: slider
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#slid.description: A user input where the user selects a value from within a given range.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#spin.name: spinbutton
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#spin.description: A form of range that expects the user to select from among discrete choices.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#stat.name: status
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#stat.description: A type of live region whose content is advisory information for the user but is not important enough to justify an alert, often but not necessarily presented as a status bar.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#swit.name: switch
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#swit.description: A type of checkbox that represents on/off values, as opposed to checked/unchecked values. See related checkbox.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tab.name: tab
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tab.description: A grouping label providing a mechanism for selecting the tab content that is to be rendered to the user.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tabl.name: table
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tabl.description: A section containing data arranged in rows and columns. See related grid.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tabl.name: tablist
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tabl.description: A list of tab elements, which are references to tabpanel elements.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tabp.name: tabpanel
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tabp.description: A container for the resources associated with a tab, where each tab is contained in a tablist.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#term.name: term
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#term.description: A word or phrase with a corresponding definition. See related definition.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#text.name: textbox
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#text.description: A type of input that allows free-form text as its value.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#time.name: timer
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#time.description: A type of live region containing a numerical counter which indicates an amount of elapsed time from a start point, or the time remaining until an end point.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tool.name: toolbar
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tool.description: A collection of commonly used function buttons or controls represented in compact visual form.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tool.name: tooltip
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tool.description: A contextual popup that displays a description for an element.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tree.name: tree
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tree.description: A type of list that may contain sub-level nested groups that can be collapsed and expanded.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tree.name: treegrid
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tree.description: A grid whose rows can be expanded and collapsed in the same manner as for a tree.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tree.name: treeitem
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#tree.description: An option item of a tree. This is an element within a tree that may be expanded or collapsed if it contains a sub-level group of tree item elements.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#widg.name: widget
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#widg.description: An interactive component of a graphical user interface (GUI).

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: true/false
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: Value representing either true or false. The default value for this value type is false unless otherwise specified.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: tristate
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: Value representing true or false, with an intermediate "mixed" value. The default value for this value type is false unless otherwise specified.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: true/false/undefined
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: Value representing true, false, or not applicable. For example, an element with aria-expanded set to false is not currently expanded; an element with aria-expanded set to undefined is not expandable. The default value for this value type is undefined unless otherwise specified.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: ID reference
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: Reference to the ID of another element in the same document

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: ID reference list
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: A list of one or more ID references.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: integer
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: A numerical value without a fractional component.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: token
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: One of a limited set of allowed values. An explicit value of undefined for this type is the equivalent of providing no value.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: token list
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: A list of one or more tokens.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.name: URI
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#valu.description: A Uniform Resource Identifier as defined by RFC 3986 [RFC3986]. It may reference a separate document, or a content fragment identifier in a separate document, or a content fragment identifier within the same document.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-activedescendant
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Identifies the currently active element when DOM focus is on a composite widget, textbox, group, or application.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-atomic
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Indicates whether assistive technologies will present all, or only parts of, the changed region based on the change notifications defined by the aria-relevant attribute.

values.description: Assistive technologies will present only the changed node or nodes.
Assistive technologies will present the entire changed region as a whole, including the author-defined label if one exists.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-autocomplete
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Indicates whether inputting text could trigger display of one or more predictions of the user's intended value for an input and specifies how predictions would be presented if they are made.

values.description: When a user is providing input, text suggesting one way to complete the provided input may be dynamically inserted after the caret.
When a user is providing input, an element containing a collection of values that could complete the provided input may be displayed.

When a user is providing input, an element containing a collection of values that could complete the provided input may be displayed. If displayed, one value in the collection is automatically selected, and the text needed to complete the automatically selected value appears after the caret in the input.
When a user is providing input, an automatic suggestion that attempts to predict how the user intends to complete the input is not displayed.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-busy
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Indicates an element is being modified and that assistive technologies MAY want to wait until the modifications are complete before exposing them to the user.

values.description: There are no expected updates for the element.
The element is being updated.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-checked
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Indicates the current "checked" state of checkboxes, radio buttons, and other widgets. See related aria-pressed and aria-selected.

values.description: The element supports being checked but is not currently checked.
Indicates a mixed mode value for a tri-state checkbox or menuitemcheckbox.
The element is checked.
The element does not support being checked.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-colcount
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Defines the total number of columns in a table, grid, or treegrid. See related aria-colindex.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-colindex
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Defines an element's column index or position with respect to the total number of columns within a table, grid, or treegrid. See related aria-colcount and aria-colspan.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-colspan
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Defines the number of columns spanned by a cell or gridcell within a table, grid, or treegrid. See related aria-colindex and aria-rowspan.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-controls
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Identifies the element (or elements) whose contents or presence are controlled by the current element. See related aria-owns.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-current
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Indicates the element that represents the current item within a container or set of related elements.

values.description: Represents the current page within a set of pages.
Represents the current step within a process.
Represents the current location within an environment or context.
Represents the current date within a collection of dates.
Represents the current time within a set of times.
Represents the current item within a set.
Does not represent the current item within a set.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-describedby
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Identifies the element (or elements) that describes the object. See related aria-labelledby.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-details
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Identifies the element that provides a detailed, extended description for the object. See related aria-describedby.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-disabled
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: Indicates that the element is perceivable but disabled, so it is not editable or otherwise operable. See related aria-hidden and aria-readonly.

values.description: The element is enabled.
The element and all focusable descendants are disabled and its value cannot be changed by the user.

https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.name: aria-dropeffect
https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria.description: [Deprecated in ARIA 1.1] Indicates what functions can be performed when a dragged object is released on the drop target.

values.description: A duplicate of the source object will be dropped into the target.
A function supported by the drop target is executed, using the drag source as an input.
A reference or shortcut to the dragged object will be created in the target object.
The source object will be removed from its current location and dropped into the target.
